<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
Wingman — "Wingman in Control" banner UI component (W7 Autopilot mode).

This component is mounted by the W7 Autopilot mode when the user engages
full UI lock. It surfaces a persistent banner with a "Take Back Control"
button so the player can reverse the AI takeover at any time.

Layout:
  - A small horizontal banner anchored to the top-right of the campaign UI
    (campaign_banners_docker, sibling of the message-event panel).
  - Contains one text label ("Wingman is in control") and one button
    (id = "button_take_back").

Wiring (in script/campaign/mod/wingman_ai.lua):
  - show_banner() calls core:get_or_create_component("wingman_banner",
    "UI/Campaign UI/wingman_banner.twui.xml") and SetVisible(true).
  - hide_banner() calls the same and SetVisible(false).
  - The ComponentLClickUp listener for id "button_take_back" calls
    on_take_back_button() -> wingman_ai.release_autopilot().

This is a deliberately minimal UI: one label + one button. A future
polish pass could add a faction-flag icon and a "settings" cog, but
the contract tested in test_w7_autopilot.py (Tests 8 + 9) is just
show/hide + take-back click. Keep it that simple unless the user asks
for more.
-->
<component name="wingman_banner">

  <!-- Layout root: a horizontal banner. The campaign UI anchors
       elements that are children of the top-level UI root into
       wherever the engine decides. We use a banner_template row. -->
  <template type="banner_template">
    <child_component_context />
    <event id="banner_event" name="banner_event" />
  </template>

  <!-- The label is purely informational; no event binding. -->
  <component name="banner_label" type="text_label">
    <text_value>Wingman is in control — click to take back</text_value>
  </component>

  <!-- The take-back button. The lua side listens for ComponentLClickUp
       with context.string == "button_take_back" and calls
       wingman_ai.release_autopilot(). -->
  <component name="button_take_back" type="button">
    <text_value>Take Back Control</text_value>
  </component>

</component>
